modules.description: Provides functions to parse, validate, and manipulate relative hyperlink references, including resolving relative paths against base URLs and normalizing href strings. Works with strings representing URLs and path components, handling edge cases like multiple slashes and dot segments. Used to process hyperlinks in HTML documents or XML feeds, ensuring consistent navigation within a site's structure.

Rewrites absolute URIs in href attributes to relative forms, specifically converting document-internal links from `docURI#id` to `#id`. Processes HTML elements to modify attribute values in place. Supports direct manipulation of node attributes and URI normalization. Can transform `https://example.com/page.html#section1` into `#section1` within the same document.
